This paper is about Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper specifically focuses on extending the QANet architecture to cope with unanswerable questions, which involves techniques related to deep learning, neural networks, and language modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP, information retrieval, and text analysis. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all relevant to the techniques and methods used in the paper.
